  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA87">
<l>iṉiyār pukuvā reḻunaraka vācaṉ</l>
<l>muṉiyātu mūrittāḷ kōmiṉ – kaṉicāyak</l>
<l>kaṉṟeṟinta tōḷāṉ kaṉaikaḻalē kāṇpataṟku</l>
<l>naṉkaṟinta nāvalañcūḻ nāṭu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Who will now enter the gate to the seven hells? Without disgust, close</l>
<l>the strong bar. For seeing the [feet with] tinkling anklets of him</l>
<l>with the arms that threw the calf so that the fruit perished,</l>
<l>[there] is the well-known Nāvala land surrounded [by the sea].<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">nāvalam has to be interpreted as the adjectival form of nāval, the Jamun plum (Eugenia jambolana), in combination with nāṭu, “land”, a calque of Sanskrit jambudvīpa, “the continent of the Jamun plum”, that is, India.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
